{"id":36298,"title":"Right thoracotomy, off-pump, scimitar syndrome repair in infants.","abstract":"Two cases of scimitar syndrome in children under one-year old are presented. Both were repaired through a right thoracotomy, off-pump, reimplanting the venous collector in the left atrium. Tips and advantages are discussed.","date":"2014-03-03","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24585918","annotations":[{"name":"Left atrium","weight":0.422038,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Left_atrium"},{"name":"Infant","weight":0.382633,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infant"},{"name":"Thoracotomy","weight":0.315777,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thoracotomy"},{"name":"Vein","weight":0.199711,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vein"},{"name":"Atrium (heart)","weight":0.0580392,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atrium_(heart)"},{"name":"Scimitar syndrome","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scimitar_syndrome"},{"name":"Scimitar","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scimitar"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Collecting","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collecting"}]}
